    "description": "Currently, the dx for each grid is calculated from its left and right edges. I've found that this occasionally gives rise to floating point errors that cause crashes for simulations that use cgs units. Since Orion and the other BoxLib codes all store the cell spacing in the data dump anyway, why not just use the value that gets read in instead of recalculating it and risking floating point errors?  \r\n\r\nI tested this on Orion data, but I went ahead and made the change to Nyx, Castro, and Maestro as well. If people with access to those datasets could briefly check to see wheter I've screwed anything up in those frontends, that would be great. ",
